                     "topFinding":  "Sixteen patches landed since the last review and almost all of it is refactor and repair, not new M1 feature work: the hud.gd god-file extraction sweep (a real 463-line drop, 2381 to 1918) plus the iso_grid enemy-render pull, and a five-patch pathfinding/collision fix chain (v0.59.22 through v0.59.26, one reverted). The shipped game still builds, ships, saves, and plays the full M1 survival loop end-to-end. This run surfaced three gaps worth attention: the pathfinding fix chain broke the two-failed-fix rule (five eyeball-verified patches on one symptom, no instrumentation, no test coverage on the churniest module); saves are written non-atomically (open-truncate then write, no temp-and-rename, no backup) on the exact FUSE mount whose truncation is this project\u0027s worst documented hazard; and the milestone tracker is stuck at 50% while the M1 backlog is fully closed, a stale anchor rather than real drift. The lone carried HIGH (dashboard audit block shipping null from the AUDIT-*.md glob) is now open three runs and is a display bug, not runtime breakage. Verdict stays in-progress: nothing in the shipped game is broken; the work now is to test the pathfinding, harden the save write, and make the 50% honest.",
